{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"hexangular-mystical-banteng","description":"## Why\n\n`reconciler.baseline_dual_write` and `reconciler.baseline_consumer_swap` are the\nshadow/consume phase flags of the convergence rollout (epic 3006-e198 / story a118).\nBoth are now flipped ON in this project and have run clean in production, so the\nphased switches have served their purpose. Retire them and hardcode always-on\n(baseline always dual-written AND always consumed as the outbound field-differ's\narbitration ancestor).\n\n## What\n\n- Remove both fields + validators from `ReconcilerConfig` (`_config_schema.py:399,403`\n  and parser `:533,534`).\n- Hardcode always-consume: `outbound_fields.py:418-419` unconditionally reads\n  `binding_store.get_baseline(local_id)` as `arbitration_prev`; collapse the boolean\n  threading through `run_differs.py:458/473`, `outbound_differ.py:374/626/731/805`.\n- Hardcode always-dual-write at `reconcile.py:938-954`; remove the now-unreachable\n  shadow/equivalence machinery (`baseline_shadow.py`) if fully dead.\n- Remove the two lines from `rebar.toml` (`:65`, `:70`).\n- Do NOT delete `prev_snapshot`/`prev_jira_fields` â€” still needed to advance/seed baselines.\n\n## Scope\n\nBackward-compat verdict: SAFE. Baseline is persisted additively into `bindings.json`\n(no store-version bump; older binaries ignore the extra keys, per ADR-0026), the\nreconciler is a single advisory-locked GHA host process (no old-clone race), and\nneither flag changes the shape of anything written to Jira or the tickets branch.\nOut of scope: the KEEP decisions (signature mirror, completion floor).\n\n## Cold-start note (address, don't skip)\n\n`seed_baselines_from_snapshot()` exists but is never called, so a repo upgrading from\na version that never dual-wrote gets `get_baseline()==None` â†’ \"local-wins\" until\nbaselines populate lazily (could silently revert a concurrent Jira edit on first\npasses). Either wire the seed on first always-on pass, or document the one-pass\nwarm-up window explicitly.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `baseline_dual_write` + `baseline_consumer_swap` removed from schema, parser, and `rebar.toml`.\n- [ ] Baseline dual-write and consume are unconditional; boolean threading collapsed; no dead back-out branch remains.\n- [ ] Dead shadow machinery (`baseline_shadow.py`) removed if fully unreachable, or a comment records why it stays.\n- [ ] Cold-start local-wins window is either seeded or documented.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass; reconcile dry-run behaves identically to today.","id":"d6bd-95c9-65f4-442d","parent_id":"8d27-7ee1-f137-4b88","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Retire the two reconciler baseline rollout configs -> hardcode always-on"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783967892603386001,"uuid":"4a949dd4-146c-4a18-b2b0-8543ed9cc876"}